        maatPrinciple: 'Sacred Service',
        cosmicContext: '''
The first decan established the word.
The second decan carries it.
In the older Kemetic religious world, order is not maintained by declaration alone but by continued offering, duty, and correct action.
Day 11 is the handoff from speech into service.
What you named must now be carried.
Today favors dedication, usefulness, and labor offered under something greater than ego.
''',
        decanFlow: thothIIFlowRows,
        meduNeter: MeduNeterKey(
          glyph:
              '𓋴 (Ka in motion) — force carried outward in rightful proportion',
          colorFrequency:
              'Deep gold and warm copper — energy in motion, not hoarded',
          mantra: '"What I carry, I carry in service."',
        ),
      ),
