      month: month,
      flowRows: kaHerKaIIFlowRows,
      entries: [
        (
          totalDay: 11,
          starCluster:
              '✨ the heart of the bindings — cords no longer at the edge, but gathered at the center',
          maatPrinciple: 'Enter the Center Hold',
          cosmicContext: '''
The first decan tied the structure.
This second decan moves inward.
ḥry-ib msḥtjw is the heart of the fastening — the place where the bindings are no longer external supports but the living center of the whole arrangement.
Day 11 asks what now sits at the middle of your life and actually holds it together.
This is not surface order. It is core order.
What is central enough that, if it loosens, everything around it begins to drift?
That is what this decan is for.
You are no longer tying the outer rope. You are tending the central knot.
''',
          glyph: 'central knot within a ring of cords',
          colorFrequency: 'deep indigo, black earth, and concentrated gold',
          mantra: '"I protect what holds the center."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 12,
          starCluster: '✨ the bound center watched from all sides',
          maatPrinciple: 'Protect the Core',
          cosmicContext: '''
Once the center is named, it must be guarded.
Not everything deserves equal access to the core of your life.
The heart of the bindings stays strong because it is not left open to every demand, distraction, and leak.
Day 12 is about perimeter discipline around what matters most.
What is central should not be handled casually.
''',
          glyph: 'ring wall around a tied knot',
          colorFrequency: 'dark blue and gold',
          mantra: '"I guard the center from waste."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 13,
          starCluster:
              '✨ the heart of the cord-system fed so it does not dry and crack',
          maatPrinciple: 'Feed the Binding',
          cosmicContext: '''
A thing can be properly bound and still weaken if it is not fed.
Core structures need fuel: time, money, ritual, attention, repair, appreciation, rest.
Day 13 is not defensive. It is nutritive.
You strengthen the center not only by guarding it, but by feeding it what lets it remain alive.
''',
          glyph: 'offering bowl beneath a central knot',
          colorFrequency: 'bronze, gold, and fertile black',
          mantra: '"What I want to last, I feed."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 14,
          starCluster: '✨ inner tension showing itself before the rope snaps',
          maatPrinciple: 'Remove Hidden Strain',
          cosmicContext: '''
Not all danger announces itself.
Sometimes the center looks intact while quiet strain accumulates underneath it.
Day 14 is for pressure you can feel but have not named.
The point is early correction.
What is seen early can be relieved cleanly. What is ignored at the core becomes a future break.
''',
          glyph: 'tightening cord with one stress line exposed',
          colorFrequency: 'dark red-gold and indigo',
          mantra: '"I address pressure before it becomes breakage."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 15,
          starCluster: '✨ the center named not only by force, but by law',
          maatPrinciple: 'Re-state the Inner Law',
          cosmicContext: '''
A core without a law becomes mood-driven.
Day 15 returns the center to principle.
What rule, vow, truth, or standard governs this structure?
Say it again.
The inner law keeps the binding from becoming arbitrary.
It reminds you why the center deserves protection at all.
''',
          glyph: 'heart beneath a spoken rule-sign',
          colorFrequency: 'gold and deep black',
          mantra: '"The center is governed by law, not mood."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 16,
          starCluster: '✨ the core space purified so the binding stays sound',
          maatPrinciple: 'Keep the Core Clean',
          cosmicContext: '''
What is central cannot stay strong if rot is permitted to gather around it.
Resentment, clutter, contradiction, stale habits, hidden disorder — these weaken a core from the inside.
Day 16 is cleansing close to the center.
Not a full purge of life. Just removal of what should never have been allowed that close.
''',
          glyph: 'purified center-ring around tied cord',
          colorFrequency: 'black, gold, and pale blue',
          mantra: '"I keep the center clear."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 17,
          starCluster:
              '✨ strength produced by repeated tightening, not one heroic pull',
          maatPrinciple: 'Strengthen Through Repetition',
          cosmicContext: '''
What keeps the center stable is often not one grand act, but one faithful act repeated.
Day 17 honors recurrence.
The central structure becomes trustworthy because it keeps being maintained in the same rightful way.
Repetition here is not boredom. It is reinforcement.
''',
          glyph: 'repeated knot marks in a straight line',
          colorFrequency: 'soft gold over indigo',
          mantra: '"What I repeat in truth becomes strong."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 18,
          starCluster: '✨ subtle looseness detected before the center shifts',
          maatPrinciple: 'Guard Against Drift',
          cosmicContext: '''
The center rarely collapses all at once.
Usually it drifts first.
A small compromise, a delayed maintenance, a slight carelessness, a forgotten rule.
Day 18 is watchfulness.
You look for the earliest signs that the core is beginning to loosen and correct them before they widen.
''',
          glyph: 'watchful eye over central knot',
          colorFrequency: 'blue-black and gold',
          mantra: '"I notice drift while it is still small."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 19,
          starCluster:
              '✨ the central structure now carrying weight on your behalf',
          maatPrinciple: 'Let the Structure Support You',
          cosmicContext: '''
A strong center should eventually relieve you, not only depend on you.
Day 19 asks whether you are allowing the system, vow, bond, or arrangement you built to actually support you back.
If you keep carrying everything by hand, you do not yet trust the structure.
Today is for leaning, not abandoning.
Receiving support from what is sound.
''',
          glyph: 'supported heart within ringed cord',
          colorFrequency: 'warm gold and fertile black',
          mantra: '"What is sound may now support me."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 20,
          starCluster:
              '✨ the inner knot sealed at the heart of the whole arrangement',
          maatPrinciple: 'Seal the Inner Knot',
          cosmicContext: '''
The second Ka-her-Ka decan closes with the center named, guarded, fed, cleaned, and strengthened.
What was tied outwardly in the first ten days has now been secured inwardly.
This is the point where the central knot stops feeling provisional.
It has become part of the living order of your life.
Day 20 is for acknowledgment: the core now holds with more truth than it did before.
Protect it accordingly.
''',
          glyph: 'sealed inner knot within ordered circle',
          colorFrequency: 'concentrated gold and deep indigo',
          mantra: '"The center now holds."',
        ),
      ],
    );
  }

  static Map<String, KemeticDayInfo> _buildKaHerKaIIIEntries() {
    const month = 'Ka-her-Ka (Kꜣ-ḥr-Kꜣ)';
    return _buildGeneratedDecanEntries(
      keyPrefix: 'kaherka',
      decan: 3,
      decanLabel: 'Ka-her-Ka III',
      monthLabelForDate: 'Ka-her-Ka',
      month: month,
      flowRows: kaHerKaIIIFlowRows,
      entries: [
        (
          totalDay: 21,
          starCluster:
              '✨ sbꜣ msḥtjw — the fastening no longer hidden at the core, but visible as pattern and form',
          maatPrinciple: 'Work as Offering',
          cosmicContext: '''
The first decan bound what mattered.
The second secured the inner knot.
This third decan turns that held life outward into visible making.
In the Pyramid Texts, the restored one is not only protected; he is tended, alive, moving, and his house is made firm.
So Day 21 is not passive gratitude. It is labor in alignment.
What you build, clean, repair, sort, raise, document, and stabilize now becomes part of ordered life.
Treat the work like priest-work, not like meaningless chores.
''',
          glyph: 'scribe’s palette and papyrus roll beside the finished pillar',
          colorFrequency: 'Ink black on gold',
          mantra: '"My work is real and witnessed."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 22,
          starCluster:
              '✨ the visible work begins with gathered means, not scattered force',
          maatPrinciple: 'Gather the Materials',
          cosmicContext: '''
No structure rises from wish alone.
Today is the gathering day: tools, agreements, supplies, cash, time, people, and usable attention.
Kemetic order depends on preparation before lifting.
What is gathered properly enters form with less waste, less panic, and less collapse.
The build begins before the wall appears. It begins when the needed pieces stop living in separate places.
''',
          glyph: 'gathered tools laid in order',
          colorFrequency: 'clay brown, bronze, and dark blue',
          mantra: '"I gather before I raise."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 23,
          starCluster: '✨ form begins where the boundary is honestly marked',
          maatPrinciple: 'Mark the Ground',
          cosmicContext: '''
Nothing stable rises from vague edges.
Today is for marking where this thing actually begins and ends.
A build needs footprint. A vow needs boundary. A room needs placement. A system needs defined limits.
Kemetic order is always shaped.
This day favors outline before elevation — the frame that tells the coming structure where to stand.
''',
          glyph: 'marked foundation line',
          colorFrequency: 'pale gold on black earth',
          mantra: '"I give the form a true place to stand."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 24,
          starCluster:
              '✨ the first visible standing piece — rough, real, no longer imagined',
          maatPrinciple: 'Raise the First Form',
          cosmicContext: '''
Today the thing leaves the invisible.
The older texts care deeply about what is established, made firm, and brought into standing form.
That is the energy here.
The first wall, the first screen, the first page, the first ritual sequence, the first schedule lived in reality.
It does not need to be perfect. It needs to be standing.
What is rough but real has more life in it than what is polished but never raised.
''',
          glyph: 'upright pillar in first form',
          colorFrequency: 'stone gold and shadow blue',
          mantra: '"What I raise becomes real."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 25,
          starCluster:
              '✨ the standing form now inscribed with law and intention',
          maatPrinciple: 'Carve the Meaning In',
          cosmicContext: '''
A structure without meaning can still function, but it will not carry spirit well.
Day 25 is inscription.
Not always literal carving, but the placing of declared purpose into the build.
What is this for. Who does it serve. What law governs it.
This is where usefulness gains soul.
The form should not only stand; it should say something true.
''',
          glyph: 'carved sign on a standing pillar',
          colorFrequency: 'ink black on warm gold',
          mantra: '"My structure carries meaning."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 26,
          starCluster: '✨ the build tested at its joints and stress lines',
          maatPrinciple: 'Stabilize the Build',
          cosmicContext: '''
After raising and meaning comes reinforcement.
A thing may be visible and still not be safe.
Today is for joints, seams, permissions, money flow, weak edges, structural leaks.
The question is simple: where could this fail if left as it is.
Stability is part of reverence.
What serves life should not be left wobbling through neglect.
''',
          glyph: 'sealed joints along a standing frame',
          colorFrequency: 'bronze, black, and deep blue',
          mantra: '"I shore up what must endure."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 27,
          starCluster:
              '✨ the completed form now made welcoming, not merely functional',
          maatPrinciple: 'Beautify With Purpose',
          cosmicContext: '''
The build can now receive surface.
Not vanity — invitation.
Color, scent, polish, finish, softness, and visual coherence are allowed once the structure truly stands.
Kemetic order does not separate the useful from the beautiful as sharply as modern life often does.
A thing may serve better because it is also pleasing to enter, hold, or use.
Beauty here is the final language of care.
''',
          glyph: 'polished vessel at a finished threshold',
          colorFrequency: 'warm gold, lotus blue, and matte black',
          mantra: '"Beauty completes what service began."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 28,
          starCluster: '✨ the finished form formally handed upward',
          maatPrinciple: 'Consecrate / Dedicate',
          cosmicContext: '''
Today the build is offered.
Whatever was raised, repaired, stabilized, or prepared is now named as more than private effort.
A dedication keeps the work from collapsing back into mere utility.
You thank helpers, conditions, timing, materials, and Source.
Consecration is acknowledgment that you did not make this alone.
''',
          glyph: 'offering hands beneath the finished form',
          colorFrequency: 'gold and incense-black',
          mantra: '"I dedicate what was built through me."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 29,
          starCluster:
              '✨ the build now entering ordinary life without losing sacred use',
          maatPrinciple: 'Integration Into Daily Life',
          cosmicContext: '''
A structure is not complete when it looks good.
It is complete when it begins to serve daily life without collapsing.
Today is integration.
Use it. Live in it. Run the system. Enter the room. Keep the time. Let the thing do what it was built to do.
What becomes part of rhythm has a better chance of enduring than what remains ceremonial only.
''',
          glyph: 'opened threshold with ankh inside',
          colorFrequency: 'lived-in gold and earth brown',
          mantra: '"What I built now serves life."',
        ),
        (
          totalDay: 30,
          starCluster: '✨ the standing form witnessed, named, and remembered',
          maatPrinciple: 'Witness and Record',
          cosmicContext: '''
The third Ka-her-Ka decan closes with testimony.
What was held, raised, stabilized, beautified, dedicated, and integrated should now be witnessed.
The older materials join tending with making firm, and making firm with continued life.
Recording completes that movement.
You document not to flatter yourself, but to keep the work from becoming vapor.
A witnessed structure enters memory more securely than an unwitnessed one.
This is how effort becomes legacy.
''',
          glyph: 'scribe’s palette and papyrus roll beside the finished pillar',
          colorFrequency: 'ink black on gold',
          mantra: '"My work is real and witnessed."',
        ),
      ],
    );
  }

